{"id":174,"parent_id":172,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":174,"title":"James 3: Taming the Tongue","subtitle":"","short_title":"James 3: Taming the Tongue","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue"},[".heading",{"id":"head3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.head3"},["h1","James 3"],[".subtitle","Taming the Tongue"],[".intro","Have you ever been deeply hurt by something someone said to or about you? Who do you think was hurt more—you or the person who said it? A basic teaching of James’ epistle is the need to control the tongue (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/1.19,26"},"James 1:19, 26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3.10"},"3:10"],"). As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3"},"James 3"],", try to determine why what we say can keep us from perfection."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.f6"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3"},"James 3"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Helm"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Rudder"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Listeth"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Desires, wants to go"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Kindleth"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Burns"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Defileth the whole body"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Destroys or makes unclean"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Similitude"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Likeness"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Endued with knowledge"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Intelligent or experienced"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Conversation"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Conduct"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Sensual"],"(v. 15)"],["td","Lustful"],["td"]]]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.f7"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",[".",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-155-3.gif"}]]],["td",[".",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-155-4.gif"}]]]]]]],[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","A small bit, placed properly in its mouth, can guide a powerful horse. Similarly, a small rudder can direct or steer a very large ship."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.p40"},"Do the following activity as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3"},"James 3"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Tame Your Tongue"],["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-3-taming-the-tongue.p41"},"What we say is important. It is a window to our hearts. Kind and uplifting words come from pure thoughts and good feelings; evil and hurtful words come from evil thoughts and bad feelings. Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/3.1-13"},"James 3:1–13"],"and list at least three phrases that reflect different ideas about controlling what we say."]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
